<gco:CharacterString>All recreationally caught billfish and swordfish that are landed outside of a registered tournament must be reported to the National Marine Fisheries Service (NMFS). Recreational fishermen may report through a webpage or by calling the Highly Migratory Species (HMS) Recreational Reporting Line.  Webpage submissions automatically update the database; reports that are called in are manually entered by HMS staff.  Data elements collected include species landed, date of landing, date of fishing trip, port of landing, vessel name, vessel permit number, fish length, fish weight, type of trip (charter/private), fishing technique, bait type, fight time, number and species of fish released.   </gco:CharacterString>          </gmd:abstract>          <gmd:purpose>             <gco:CharacterString>Monitoring for the International Commission for the Conservation of Atlantic Tunas (ICCAT) recommendations or stock assessment needs (swordfish quota monitoring, marlin and roundscale spearfish landings monitoring and accounting against the 250 blue and white marlin/roundscale spearfish recreational limit, landings of billfishes and swordfish included in stock assessments)   </gco:CharacterString>
